{"word":"χαυνότης","slug":"χαυνότης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>χαυνότης</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:χαῦνος'><el>χαῦνος</el></a>\n<el>(χαυνότης, ητος, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:χαυνόω'><el>χαυνόω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>porousness, sponginess</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>empty vanity</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}